<h1>Filament Foundry Guides</h1>
<p>Filament Foundry helps 3D printing enthusiasts track filament, monitor usage, and reduce waste.</p>

<section>
<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<ul>
<li>Add your filament types, colors, and quantities.</li>
<li>Log the printer and filament used for each print.</li>
<li>Monitor material usage over time.</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Managing Inventory</h2>
<ul>
<li>Update filament stock after each print.</li>
<li>Remove or archive depleted spools.</li>
<li>Set alerts for low filament levels.</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Tracking Projects</h2>
<ul>
<li>Log project details (printer, filament, settings).</li>
<li>Mark prints as successful or failed.</li>
<li>Analyze filament usage trends.</li>
</ul>
</section>

